			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Kokichi's E3 Report (Day 1) 
<br />

<br />
Okey dokey...I'm sitting here in my friend's dorm room in Cal Tech typing this up at 12:53AM in the morning, so excuse me if some of my grammar is off 
<br />

<br />
Well, I survived my very first day of my very first E3, and wow, it's great! I got to play a bunch of games: 
<br />

<br />

<br />
Gamecube: Donkey Konga, Viewtiful Joe 2, Starfox 2, Metroid Prime 2: Echoes, Paper Mario 2 
<br />

<br />
GBA SP: The Legend of Zelda: Minishing Hat (something about shrinking...it's weird), Mario Pinball (Mario = the pinball), Pokemon Fire / Leaf, a few Mega Man games, and Kirby: Mirror Land (or whatever it's called). 
<br />

<br />
Xbox: Conker (sequal to Conker's Bad Fur Day), TMNT 2 (played that on GCN also), Fable, KOTOR 2....no Halo 2, unfortunately, that's only for special media members. 
<br />

<br />
PS2: Jak 3, Rachet and Clank 3, Sly Cooper 2, Eye Toy: DDR, Eye Toy: Sega, and a few others. 
<br />

<br />
PSP (yup, I got to play the PSP ^_^): Some new Metal Gear Solid game. 
<br />

<br />
Nintendo DS: Didn't get to play yesterday....today I'll be heading there first thing in the morning, there's a huge line you wait in, they take in 70 people, you watch trailers for 15 minutes and meet the voice of Mario / Luigi / others, then 20 / 70 people get selected to play the NDS. *Hopes he's one of them* 
<br />

<br />
PC: Various games....can't remember them all. However, I did play EVERQUEST II 
<br />

<br />

<br />
Okay, that stuff aside, I'll get to the stuff I learned about EQ2 today for all you fan boys out there Well, schwag wise I picked up TWO EverQuest 2 T-Shirts (one for myself and one for my friend), ONE EverQuest 2 "Babes of Norrath" calendar, and some miscellaneous EQ2 / SOE stuff. SOE's booth is pretty cool...it has a giant spider in the front that I took my picture with (made it so it looks like the spider is eating me). I thought I saw Faarwolf, so I took a picture, but I realized that Faarwolf wasn't working at the booth.....darn. My quest continues. Oh, and I asked some of the SOE workers "Do you know where Moorgard or Faarwolf are?" and their reply was "Steve left already, who's Faarwolf??". Faarwolf, this would be so much easier if I knew your name If you see a big, tall, burly, handsome guy in a grey T-shirt and shorts tomorrow with a bag full of swag, that'll be me. Say hi, won't you? 
<br />

<br />
Anyways, there's some blocked off path way into the heart of the SOE booth. You need to be media or have some kind of invintation to get in. They have a buff black bouncer there....very intimidating, not someone I really want to mess with lol. Moorgard, think I can get the a-okay to get in and check out that demo inside? 
<br />

<br />
Anyways, I also got to see a few new EQ2 movies playing on the big screen above the SOE booth. One seems to be the intro movie to EQ2 (and yes, it's new, and **bleep** it's SOOOOOOO cool), and the other one is the movie that the new screen shots were taken of (the one with the blue and gold dragon, demon creatures, etc.). Cool shizzo. 
<br />

<br />
Anyways I'm glad that I asked one of the SOE booth workers how to get inside, since he told me that EQ2 was being demoed over at the Microsoft Games booth and at the Nvidia booth. I swear I pulled out a teleportation spell and transported myself there in an instant, since that's about how long it took me to get to the Microsoft Games booth. 
<br />

<br />
There I saw a poster. It was primarily red with a lady and a guy on front. "SWEET, EQ2!!" I thought to myself. "OMG, the seat is empty!" I plopped down, looked at the screen, then realized what had happened.....in my rush I had sat down at the Guild Wars demo. Doh. So as not to be rude, I let the guy there guide me along a quest, all the while bouncing my knee, waiting to play EQ2....the game to my immediate left. 
<br />

<br />
Anyways, after that was over I watched some guy talk to Gordon Wrinn about EQ / EQ2. Once that guy got up out of the seat and left I sat down, placed my hand on the mouse, and moved the cursor. Suddenly I was in a white tunnel with a bright light at the end. 
<br />

<br />
I was at the character creation screen. Instantly I clicked on evil, then male, then Ratonga (no Frogloks / Erudites, unfortunately). There I fiddled around with the character creation and made my character, Kokichi (I realize now that in my haste I forgot to change all that I could...I didn't even look at the glasses!). 
<br />

<br />
All I really had time to do was the beginning tutorial (the one on the boat). The Ratonga running action was messed up...the game kept bouncing / shaking up and down as I ran. Gordon said that he was surprised that passed QA and was actually on the demo, but thought that perhaps a server reboot or something would fix it. Regardless, I played on through the tutorial (which isn't really all that long, but kinda boring, even though I really wanted to savor every moment I just skipped most of the boring text). When I finally got on land, Gordon suggested that I give it up to someone else....yeah yeah, fine, but I'll be back first thing today, Gordon, I promise! 
<br />

<br />
Okay....now, to sum it up, I'll make a bullet list of key notes / random facts that I learned, as well as something for all you forum members 
<br />

<br />
KOKICHI'S ULTIMATE FIRST DAY SUMMARY OF EQ2 
<br />

<br />

<br />
<span style="text-decoration: underline"><span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="color: yellow">SOE is going to release the character customization program in advance, as a free download, to the actual game. This way you can create characters, save the customization, then upload it when you install EQ2. That way you don't have to waste time creating your character. Gordon said that the first day he played it he spent about 3 hours making his character and checking out various characters (he said he likes to keep clicking the random button), and by the time he made his character, it was time to stop playing. This whole release-character-customization is an answer to that solution. Whether or not this will include names I do not know....I'll ask him tomorrow. </span></span></span>
<br />

<br />
When you hit the Random button on the character customization screen, you can choose to "Lock" features; so if you see a cool hair style you want, you can lock that hair style, then hit random and that hair style will stay. Neat idea 
<br />

<br />
2 jokes going around the EQ2 Dev team (according to Gordon): "You can make an entire game out of EQ2's particle system" and "You can make an entire game out of EQ2's spell system". Interpret that as you wish. 
<br />

<br />
Gordon Wrinn (I really hope I'm getting the name right....I think I am) is a programmer for EQ2. When I asked him what he did, he said something along the lines of "Play EQ2...well, I program, but it's great". Basically saying that he's really having fun programming EQ2 (whether he's forced to say that or not I do not know...) 
<br />

<br />
Gordon says that working with SOE is great, and that he loves it. 
<br />
When I asked about the heirloom system, he said that they would announce it in time that people can start up EQLive accounts / reactivate old EQLive accounts so they can still get the heirloom. Phew. He said he'd ask today and see if he could get a date or more information on that. 
<br />
For the Ratonga customization, you don't get to choose "Eye patch" or "Lip ring" or anything....instead you choose "themes", like "Rogue theme" or "Cyclopse theme". I think they might do it this way for other races as well...tomorrow I'll experiement with each race. Mwahahhaha. 
<br />

<br />
Ratonga are, actually, really small, even if you max out their height. Kutstuu....... 
<br />

<br />
Voice overs are cool....but I found myself just reading the text right away (I'm a really fast reader / typer) then hitting "Next" or whatever it said, instead of listening to the voices. I think a lot of people will end up doing this....skipping the dialogue the first time around since they realy just want to play the game, then after it's been out for a few months, gradually start listening more and more as there isn't such a huge feeling to rush rush rush and play play play. 
<br />

<br />
I really hope that they delete my character after E3....I don't want to not be able to use the name Kokichi (even though I don't think I'm going to use that name for my main...) 
<br />

<br />
After spending about an hour doing some stupid hole-punch quest, I got 2 EverQuest 2 T-shirts, both XL (I think that's all they have). The front has the NVidia logo, and the back has a picture of some EQ2 happenings with a green NVidia banner and logo on the bottom. The picture itself is cool, but the colors are, honestly, really bad. It doesn't look like they spent too much time on the colors.... 
<br />

<br />
I haven't opened up my Babes of Norrath calendar....but man, that thing is going up on my wall first thing I get back 
<br />

<br />
I plan on getting another T-Shirt tomorrow (yeah yeah, I have to do the whole stupid quest alllll over again), as well as another BoN calendar, if I can. I already promised MystikClaw that I'd give him my 2nd T-shirt, and probably another calendar if I can get one. However, any more T-shirts I get / calendars after the next one I'll figure out someway to raffle off to you guys....maybe do something like Moorgard did, I don't know, I have to still think about it more. 
<br />

<br />
Faarwolf is good at hiding....but I have my instant-camera, quick and ready in a flash! (pun intended.)
<br />

<br />
Okay, that's about it....any one have anything in specific they want me to ask someone at SOE about EQ2 if I can? I think Gordon will probably be there again...he's really cool. Actually, I'm guessing the entire staff of EQ2 is really cool. 
<br />

<br />
Oh yeah, and Stan Lee is there signing autographs. I'll get mine tomorrow Also I'll post pictures of me and all the freggin' hot booth babes....man, I can't believe I've been missing out on them! Where have all of those beautiful women been all my life? 
<br />

<br />
Oh, and I swear to god that one of the Nintendo booth chicks was hitting on me....she was smiling at me, gave me a free GBA SP headphone set (I have like, 4 of those now, lol), and we were talking for a while about the GBA-video playing devices....they fit like, 5 Spongebob Squarepants episodes onto one cartridge, as well as various anime and other TV shows. Crazy! 
<br />

<br />
If my character is still there, tomorrow I will log on him (I'll take a picture of where it says Kokichi so you all can see ) and play as much as I can. Honestly, I got the best swag there is to get yesterday....I figure I'll spend a few hours getting swag / playing other games, a few hours mingling / eating / catching up with old friends, and the rest of my hours on EQII (that is, of course, until Gordon has to drag the stool out from underneath me). 
<br />

<br />
Oh, another something I wanted to mention; 
<br />

<br />

<br />
EQ2 Internal Beta will begin a few days after E3 ends. This is the "Alpha" testing I believe....it's basically a friends and family only beta.
<br />

<br />
Oh, and when I was talking to Gordon and when I had mentioned that I was an active poster but didn't think I'd get into beta, he gave me a puzzled kind of look and asked me why. I explained to him my situation (not being able to use this account for signing up for beta since the Bday isn't mine, it's below 1, and that I had to make a new account and apply. When I mentioned that I had to make a new account to apply he sorta rolled his eyes and said "Oooh, don't worry about it, EQ2 will come out soon enough," basically confirming my suspicions of people who just made new accounts probably given least preference and active posters on the forums given some preference. **bleep**. 
<br />

<br />
Oh, and I also asked Gordon if you can remove glasses from your character when you make them on your character creation (of course I already knew the answer, but I just wanted to play dumb and see what other information I could squeeze out of him And Gordon, if you're reading this, I'm just kidding, don't hurt me, I love you! Okay, time to stop freaking you out now....). He said that you can't right now, but that it'd be really easy to make it so you can take them off and that you can buy new glasses. This might be true with piercings....I'll have to ask. So basically if you're going to play a race that wears glasses, I'd suggest that you wear them, since you'll most likely end up being able to take them off eventually (so choose cool glasses and not big, dumb goofy looking ones). 
<br />

<br />
Okay....so spells and scout abilities. Check. I'll bring a piece of paper and a pen tomorow to write all the info down so I don't forget it. And like I said, I'll try to get more EQ2 parapha- - para - - - parapha - - - swag (read that again Porky Pig style) to somehow give out to people here. Please don't PM me or email me or IM me or anything about it....I'm only giving one of the two EQ2 things I got to MystikClaw since we're buds and I already talked to him about it a few weeks in advance. I can also give away other stuff that I picked up, like special GBA SP earphones or something....I dunno, I'll see what I can get, but just know that I'm thinking of you all<span style="font-weight: bold"></span><span style="font-weight: bold"></span><br />_________________<br /><img src="http://gormsplace.homestead.com/files/gsign.jpg" border="0" /></span><span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by Gormadoc Uberscale on Fri May 14, 2004 4:50 AM; edited 2 times in total</span></td>
