				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Ensaine's E3 Write Up 
<br />

<br />
Just got back and was able to get into the EQ2 showing. 
<br />

<br />
Fortunately I have friends in the business and was able to come on in for the demo. I was able to see the actual 'trailer' that all those new ss's came from. Beautiful to say the least. On a side note, however, the game was even chugging on their demo machines. It's gonna take a monster machine to run this at full detail. I believe them when they say they are setting it up for future hardware. 
<br />

<br />
I actually played through the tutorial, the one we've all seen by now I'm sure. It was very simple and straight forward like most people have expected. The animations are superb and keep on getting better. The world itself does seem to be alive. 
<br />

<br />
Part of the demonstration was walking around town, namely Freeport. The SS of Freeport with the troops all lined up and such, yep, saw that part of town. Qeynos was really nice. They had this old man that fed ducks and the ducks would follow him around and just outta nowhere, randomly the speaker said, a cat will come out and chase one of them away and the old man kinda goes nutty over the cat chasing "his" ducks. All with full voice over as well. They had this small bridge in Qeynos where a teacher of the arcane arts was teaching children and students spellcasting. The teacher would cast a spell and the students would mimic him afterwords. All with voice over Based on what the speaker said, sometimes the students, being new to the arts I guess, would make "mistakes". Unfortunately, I didn't see mistakes this time. Good class I guess. 
<br />

<br />
They described the players that were in the demo (also in the newest ss's). I hope I remember them all correctly. They were: Barbarian Guardian, High Elf Wizard, Dark Elf Scout, and a Dwarven Cleric. I think the last one was a Half Elf (or Human, I forget) Fury. 
<br />

<br />
The dragon scene was instanced. Apparently a lot of these instances will be in the game. BTW, after that ss of the dragon breath over the players, they all turned into skeletons, and their bones just dropped to the floor. Everyone was dead. Hella cool !! 
<br />

<br />
The ss's with the lizard men and the dragon, that was the Temple of Cazic Thule. The speaker was quick to point out that the lizards poked their own eyes out for religeous purposes. (to serve their diety)<br />_________________<br /><img src="http://gormsplace.homestead.com/files/gsign.jpg" border="0" /></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
