			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">E3 Madness 
<br />
By Sassee and Knusende at EQ2Vault 
<br />

<br />
First off we would like to say that we are having a blast, everyone we have met is so cool and e3 is super exciting. Knusende and I were left to ourselves to find one another at the airport since we arrived later in the day than everyone else. LAX is a very busy airport! So our first adventure was finding each other. After I waited ten minutes for my luggage (I was close to a nervous breakdown there for a minute), and about five cell phone calls to Knusende, we finally decided just to go outside by the cabs and find each other. A fifty dollar cab ride later and a hotel check in, we then decided we could just walk to the LA Convention Center since the shuttles only run in the morning and evenings. Please remember at this time that I am a cheapskate and I have found that Knusende is as well, we are still recovering from our fifty dollar cab fare. As it turns out, the Convention Center is not as close to our hotel as we first thought, so a half an hour into our little stroll, we decided we should probably figure out a plan B as its not the greatest neighborhood for two females who are tourists. After attempting to get directions from a very kind non-english speaking lady on the street we had to resort to asking someone who spoke the same language. Lady number two informed us that there is a bus here called the Dash that only costs one quarter and runs to the Convention Center. 
<br />

<br />
The bus at first was such a relief I think I thanked the driver at least ten times. But then he stopped at another stop and thats when the bus guy got on. Everyone on the EQ2 Staff has heard about him and guess what, now you get to hear about him too. I was just a little scared of him, I cant even quote what he said to me because first of all it involved his nether regions and the rest was not comprehendible. Something about punk rockers and hippies we are really not sure. Needless to say, we were really thankful when he got off the bus. Finally we found ourselves at the Convention Center and got to see just how big E3 is. Deathstryker and his wife were the first to come find us because he had our passes. It was pretty funny because we were outside and apparently I look different with short hair. So when this guy who sort of looked familiar walked by me and nonchalantly tried to see if I was Sassee or not, I figured out who he was and Knusende recognized his wife. 
<br />

<br />
He gave us a quick tour through the place and showed us the IGN room and then he was off for meetings. Knusende, DSs wife Kate and I found ourselves wandering around this huge place aimlessly. Eventually we found Loki, Nyneve, and Takasi. We did not find Drakes and Desire until later that day when we all met up in a bar. Apparently Drakes and Desi along with Philez had been in the bar for a while. *cough* -- this is when we discovered that Drakes could most likely find a career in stand-up comedy. We have cried laughing more than once just in the first day, and get this, Knusende snorts when she laughs! Drakes is keeping track of snorts and he has a point system going for how many times he can make her snort. I am not sure I want to know what the prize is at the end, but I have found a money making scheme. Drakes has offered me a dollar for every autograph I give out claiming to be Courtney Cox Arquette. Apparently I look like her *shrug*. So if you are at e3 and somehow reading this, come ask me for my autograph, I could use some extra cash seems how it costs nine bucks at least just for a sandwich and a water at the Convention food stands. 
<br />

<br />
We did get a chance to look at game stuff even though we didnt arrive until afternoon. We were given a wonderful opportunity to check out the EQ2 Booth. Outside the booth is a huge movie screen coming out of the ceiling and the movie is awesome. It shows a group taking on an encounter with a huge dragon and the combat animations are jaw dropping. Later today we are hoping to be able to enter the inside of their booth and check out more goodies and maybe get some playtime. We will defiantly let you know if that occurs. We got to take a look at some other game booths such as Dragon Empires, City of Heros, the new expansion for EQ1 (new graphics engine, looks wonderful by the way), and I should mention that there is a huge spider man model stuck to the outside of the building. This place is a lot of fun. 
<br />

<br />
Our last adventure of the night was our dinner at Barbaras at the Brewery. You should know that this place was virtually impossible to find if you are not from this city. We are directly downtown and its just slightly confusing. Needless to say a restaurant that is only a couple miles away took us over a half an hour to find. We did get some really great scenery in, like that mattress under the bridge, a cool garbage lot and we were thrilled when DS decided that he would turn around in a parking lot full of people in shower caps that looked like they were probably up to no good. Again, I was just little bit scared, good thing Knusende, Desire and I were in Drakes car. The guy is freaking hilarious. I still laugh at some of the stuff that came out of his mouth yesterday. Dinner was really fun, especially when you drink three Cosmopolitans. The best part of the day and our experience has been that we have discovered that even though not all of us have met before in real life, we are truly like old friends who can come together and have a great time. Everyone on the EQ2 Staff and everyone we have met through IGN have been awesome people. Good times for sure. 
<br />

<br />
We are really excited to get today going and get lots of pictures and more goodies for you so we will check back in later, good day!<br />_________________<br /><img src="http://gormsplace.homestead.com/files/gsign.jpg" border="0" /></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
